 1W into 8 ohms The Delta Mono is specified as being able to deliver 300W into 8 ohms and 600W into 4 ohms  and 1000W into 2 ohms  with the line voltage held constant all at 01 distortion Using our definition of clipping which is when the outputs percentage of THDnoise reaches 1 the Classé exceeded its specified powers into 8 ohms clipping with a 1kHz signal at 380W into 8 ohms  and at 610W into 4 ohms  The Delta Mono clipped at 950W into 2 ohms  however it is relevant to note that I dont hold the AC wall voltage constant when I test an amplifiers clipping power With the Delta Mono idling the wall voltage measured 1213V With the amplifier clipping into 2 ohms the supply voltage had dropped to 1175V which is why I found a slight shortfall in maximum power into this loadFig4 Classé Delta Mono distortion  vs 1kHz continuous output power into 8 ohmsFig5 Classé Delta Mono distortion  vs 1kHz continuous output power into 4 ohmsFig6 Classé Delta Mono distortion  vs 1kHz continuous output power into 2 ohmsI measured how the THDN percentage changed with frequency at 20V output which is equivalent to 50W into 8 ohms 100W into 4 ohms and 200W into 2 ohms—high enough to shift the Delta Monos output stage from classA into classAB The THDN was very low in the midrange into 8 ohms  but rose into lower impedances  However as Sergiu Ignat had said when I interviewed him the usual increase in THDN in the top audio octave is absent confirming that the amplifiers openloop bandwidth is commendably wideFig7 Classé Delta Mono THDN  vs frequency at 20V into 8 ohms  4 ohms  2 ohms The Delta Monos distortion was predominantly the subjectively benign third harmonic  This lay at –94dB  at 50Hz into 8 ohms  and while it rose to –76dB  at the same voltage into 4 ohms  the higher harmonics are all extremely low in level When the amplifier drove an equal mix of 19 and 20kHz tones at 50W into 8 ohms  the secondorder difference product at 1kHz is missing in action and higherorder intermodulation products lay at an extremely low –99dB Fig8 Classé Delta Mono 1kHz waveform at 50W into 8 ohms 00013 THDN  distortion and noise waveform with fundamental notched out Fig9 Classé Delta Mono spectrum of 50Hz sinewave DC–1kHz at 50W into 8 ohms Fig10 Classé Delta Mono spectrum of 50Hz sinewave DC–1kHz at 100W into 4 ohms Fig11 Classé Delta Mono HF intermodulation spectrum DC–30kHz 1920kHz at 50W peak into 8 ohms The Classé Delta Mono performed extremely well on the test bench a testament to its audio engineering      
